---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'Framer vs Squarespace 2025: Modern vs Established',
  description: 'Framer vs Squarespace: Framer is modern visual builder for designers ($5-40/month). Squarespace is design-first established platform ($16-65/month). Framer: components, Figma import, faster performance. Squarespace: better templates, stronger e-commerce, easier. Choose Framer for design control. Choose Squarespace for ease.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['Framer vs Squarespace', 'website builder comparison', 'no-code platforms', 'Framer review', 'Squarespace review'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#0055FF]/5 to-[#E04F5F]/5 py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#0055FF] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Website Builder Comparison · 2025
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        Framer vs Squarespace
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        Framer and Squarespace represent two different generations of website builders. Framer is the modern challenger with a component-based approach. Squarespace is the established platform with polished templates. Framer gives designers more control. Squarespace gives everyone easier results. Framer performs faster. Squarespace handles e-commerce better. Both work. Neither is universally better.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Choose Framer if you're a designer who wants visual control and Figma integration. Choose Squarespace if you want beautiful results with minimal effort and better e-commerce. Framer is cheaper for similar features. Squarespace is easier if you have zero design experience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Framer</th>
            <th class="text-left p-4 font-bold">Squarespace</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Ease of Use</td>
            <td class="p-4">Moderate learning curve</td>
            <td class="p-4">Easier, beginner-friendly</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Design Approach</td>
            <td class="p-4">Components, visual control</td>
            <td class="p-4">Templates, blocks</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Templates</td>
            <td class="p-4">Fewer, more flexible</td>
            <td class="p-4">Many, more polished</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Figma Integration</td>
            <td class="p-4">Native import</td>
            <td class="p-4">None</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Performance</td>
            <td class="p-4">Excellent, fast loading</td>
            <td class="p-4">Good, not exceptional</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">E-commerce</td>
            <td class="p-4">Basic (Stripe only)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Strong, full-featured</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">CMS</td>
            <td class="p-4">Included ($25/month+)</td>
            <td class="p-4">Built-in</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Pricing</td>
            <td class="p-4">$5-40/month</td>
            <td class="p-4">$16-65/month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b">
            <td class="p-4 font-bold">Best For</td>
            <td class="p-4">Designers, portfolios</td>
            <td class="p-4">Small businesses, e-commerce</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framer Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Component-Based Design</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer uses components like React. Create once, reuse everywhere.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Design a button, save as component, use across your site. Update once, changes apply everywhere. Modern web design workflow. Squarespace doesn't have this.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Figma Integration</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Import Figma designs directly. Layers, styles, all preserved.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Design in Figma, export to Framer. Massive workflow advantage. Squarespace has no Figma integration - you rebuild designs manually.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Better Performance</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer sites load faster. Core Web Vitals scores are stronger.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Site speed affects SEO and user experience. Framer generates optimized code automatically. Squarespace sites are fine but not exceptional.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">More Design Flexibility</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Visual editor gives you pixel-perfect control.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Squarespace templates are rigid. Framer lets you break the grid, custom layouts, unique designs. If you care about standing out, Framer delivers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Cheaper for Similar Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Framer's CMS plan ($25/month) is cheaper than Squarespace's Business plan ($36/month).</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> For portfolios and marketing sites, Framer gives you more features for less money. Squarespace only makes sense if you need e-commerce.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Squarespace Deep Dive -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Squarespace Does Well
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Better Templates</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace templates are polished, professional, and ready to use.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Framer has fewer templates. Squarespace has something for every industry. You don't need to design - just pick and customize.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Stronger E-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace has full e-commerce features. Framer has basic selling only.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you're selling products, Squarespace is the clear winner. Inventory, abandoned cart, subscriptions - Framer lacks these.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Easier for Beginners</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace is simpler. Framer has a learning curve.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> If you've never used design tools, Framer feels overwhelming. Squarespace's template approach is friendlier. Less to learn, faster results.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Built-In Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Scheduling, memberships, email marketing - all included.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Framer can do some of this with integrations. Squarespace has it built-in. Less setup, more all-in-one.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Established Platform</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Squarespace has been around longer. More mature, more stable.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Why it matters:</strong> Framer is newer and rapidly evolving. Squarespace is predictable. You know what you're getting long-term.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Free:</strong> $0 (1 page, Framer branding)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Pro:</strong> $5/month (3 pages, custom domain)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Basic:</strong> $15/month (unlimited pages, 1000 CMS items)</li>
          <li>• <strong>CMS:</strong> $25/month (unlimited CMS, localization)</li>
          <li>• <strong>CMS + Team:</strong> $40/month (team collaboration)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Annual billing:</strong> All prices shown are annual. Monthly costs 20-40% more.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-pink-50 border-2 border-pink-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">Squarespace Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>Personal:</strong> $16/month annually ($23 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Business:</strong> $23/month annually ($33 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Basic:</strong> $27/month annually ($36 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Commerce Advanced:</strong> $49/month annually ($65 monthly)</li>
          <li>• <strong>Scheduling:</strong> $23/month annually ($30 monthly)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700"><strong>Annual billing:</strong> All prices shown are annual. Monthly costs ~40% more.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When to Choose Each
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Framer If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You're a designer:</strong> Figma user who wants visual control</li>
          <li>• <strong>You use Figma:</strong> Want direct import to website builder</li>
          <li>• <strong>You care about performance:</strong> Site speed matters for SEO</li>
          <li>• <strong>Building portfolios:</strong> Design sites, marketing pages, landing pages</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want components:</strong> Reusable design elements save time</li>
          <li>• <strong>Budget matters:</strong> Framer is cheaper for similar features</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black text-xl mb-4">✅ Choose Squarespace If</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li>• <strong>You're selling products:</strong> Need full e-commerce features</li>
          <li>• <strong>You're a beginner:</strong> Have zero design experience</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want it easy:</strong> Just want something that looks good fast</li>
          <li>• <strong>You need built-in features:</strong> Scheduling, memberships, email marketing</li>
          <li>• <strong>You want templates:</strong> Don't want to design from scratch</li>
          <li>• <strong>You value stability:</strong> Want established, predictable platform</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bottom Line -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-white bg-opacity-50 border-2 border-gray-300 rounded-xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-6">Bottom Line</h2>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">Framer and Squarespace both work. Framer is the modern choice for designers. Squarespace is the established choice for everyone else. Framer gives you more control and better performance. Squarespace gives you easier results and better e-commerce.</p>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Framer for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Visual design control without code</li>
        <li>• Figma integration workflow</li>
        <li>• Component-based design system</li>
        <li>• Better site performance</li>
        <li>• Cheaper pricing for similar features</li>
        <li>• Portfolios and marketing sites</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6"><strong>Choose Squarespace for:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <li>• Beautiful templates out of the box</li>
        <li>• Strong e-commerce features</li>
        <li>• Easier beginner experience</li>
        <li>• Built-in features (scheduling, memberships)</li>
        <li>• Established, stable platform</li>
        <li>• Small businesses and online stores</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700"><strong>Can't decide?</strong> Start with Squarespace if you have zero design experience. Start with Framer if you're comfortable with design tools. Both offer free trials - test both and see which interface clicks. You can't go wrong with either choice.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/framer-review" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer Review</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Full Framer review</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/webflow-vs-wordpress" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Webflow vs WordPress</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">No-code vs open source</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
